modules.description: This module converts between host access definitions and a structured representation. It provides `of_defns` to create a host access structure from a list of definitions and `to_defns` to serialize the structure back into a list of definitions. It works with `Unistd.Access.defns`, which represents access control entries, and is used to manage host-based access control in network services.

This module converts between host-specific file seek definitions and a portable representation. It provides `of_defns` to import host-defined seek constants into a structured type, and `to_defns` to export them back. Use this when interfacing with low-level file operations that require precise control over seek behavior in different operating environments.

This module defines a data type `t` for representing host-specific system configuration definitions. It provides functions `of_defns` and `to_defns` for converting between host configurations and a generic definitions type. It is used to manage and manipulate system-specific settings in a structured way.

This module defines portable file seek operations and conversions for handling file offsets in low-level I/O. It works with integer-coded seek modes and structured types representing host-specific definitions. Use it to translate between system-specific seek constants and a unified type when implementing cross-platform file access logic.

This module manages access control permissions using bit-encoded integers and structured definitions. It provides functions to convert between permission lists and integer codes, check and set individual permissions, and interface with host-specific access definitions through the `Host` submodule. It is used to enforce fine-grained access control in network services based on host configurations.

This module provides functions to retrieve and manage host-specific system configuration values, such as memory page size. It works with a structured type representing host configurations and supports concrete operations like querying the page size in bytes. A typical use case involves determining system memory characteristics for low-level resource management.

This module implements low-level system operations for file access, seeking, and configuration queries. It works with bit-encoded permissions, file offset constants, and system-specific configuration values. Used to implement cross-platform I/O logic with precise control over file operations and system resource parameters.
